WEBVTT

00:02.436 --> 00:04.579
PREVIOUSLY ON GRACELAND...

00:04.679 --> 00:06.581
- THIS IS FRANCESCA'S RAGOUT,
AND THE RULES ARE SIMPLE--

00:06.648 --> 00:09.317
DON'T TOUCH
AND DON'T BE LATE.

00:09.384 --> 00:11.686
- I KILLED AN FBI AGENT,
AND THEY GOT IT ON TAPE.

00:11.753 --> 00:14.055
- DALE, YOU COULD GET
THREE YEARS FOR ACCESSORY.

00:14.155 --> 00:15.456
- DETECTIVE SID MARKHAM,

00:15.523 --> 00:17.458
I KNOW YOU'RE WORKING
WITH THE SOLANO CARTEL.

00:17.525 --> 00:19.460
YOU DON'T JUST RETIRE.

00:19.527 --> 00:21.596
- YOU DO IF YOU GOT A TON
OF CASH IN SAFETY-DEPOSIT BOXES.

00:21.696 --> 00:23.231
- WE ROB THE BANK.

00:23.331 --> 00:24.499
IF HIS NEST EGG
GOES UP IN SMOKE,

00:24.599 --> 00:26.200
HE'S GOT TO MAKE A MOVE.

00:26.267 --> 00:28.036
- WE HIT GETTY NATIONAL
IN ONE WEEK.

00:28.102 --> 00:29.337
- I'LL BE READY.

00:29.404 --> 00:31.372
- YOU AND LITTLE MISS FBI
HAD SOME CHEMISTRY.

00:31.472 --> 00:33.107
I'D LIKE YOU TO LEAN IN,

00:33.207 --> 00:34.676
SEE WHAT SHE'S DOING
WITH OUR SURVEILLANCE GEAR.

00:34.742 --> 00:37.278
- APPARENTLY
IT'S A SEX-TRAFFICKING RING

00:37.345 --> 00:38.680
IN SYLMAR.

00:38.746 --> 00:40.315
IT'S DEFINITELY SOLANO.

00:40.381 --> 00:41.649
HIS SON SET IT UP.

00:41.749 --> 00:44.052
IF ANYBODY FINDS OUT
I GAVE THIS TO YOU...

00:44.118 --> 00:47.388
- I WANT APPROACHES FROM
EVERY ANGLE WITHIN THE HOUR.

00:47.488 --> 00:49.023
- SULLA--
[gunshots]

00:51.626 --> 00:53.394
- EVERYBODY, HANDS UP!

00:53.494 --> 00:55.096
- MY BLONDE FRIEND
IS GONNA ASK ME

00:55.163 --> 00:57.365
WHY WE WENT IN UNDER THEIR NOSE
AND EVERYONE DIED.

00:57.432 --> 00:59.367
I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO TELL HER.
- YOU TELL HER NOTHING.

00:59.467 --> 01:01.603
GOOD JOB.
I'LL CALL YOU.

01:01.669 --> 01:03.771
- SO YOU GUYS
SCREWED ME, HUH?

01:04.072 --> 01:05.106
WE LOST EVERYTHING.

01:05.206 --> 01:08.476
- SID IS FINALLY BRINGING ME
INTO THE FOLD.

01:08.576 --> 01:10.111
CHARLIE'S PREGNANT.

01:10.211 --> 01:12.413
I REALLY WANT TO KEEP IT.

01:12.480 --> 01:13.548
SAUCE, HUH?

01:13.615 --> 01:15.016
- BEEN TOO LONG.

01:15.083 --> 01:17.418
YOU WANT TO HELP ME
CUT THE PEPPERS?

01:17.485 --> 01:19.153
[cell phone ringing]

01:19.220 --> 01:23.157
- THIS PLACE
BURNED BECAUSE OF US.

01:26.160 --> 01:29.163
AND YOU LIT THE MATCH!

01:29.263 --> 01:30.498
- STAY BACK.

01:30.565 --> 01:32.500
- GUNS NOW?

01:32.567 --> 01:34.669
[men struggling]

01:34.769 --> 01:35.703
[gunshot]

01:35.803 --> 01:38.473
[click, beep beep beep]

01:38.539 --> 01:39.774
- HEY.

01:43.544 --> 01:46.314
YEAH, OKAY.
SOUNDS GOOD.

01:50.284 --> 01:53.488
ALL RIGHT, MAN,
TALK TO YOU LATER.

01:55.690 --> 01:57.625
- WHAT DID HE SAY?

02:00.194 --> 02:02.030
HELLO?

02:02.096 --> 02:03.197
- UM...

02:03.297 --> 02:06.501
HE--HE SAID
THAT HE WANTS TO, UM...

02:06.567 --> 02:09.170
- HE WANTS YOU
TO WHAT, PAUL?

02:09.237 --> 02:12.173
- MEET TOMORROW,
AT THE OFFICE.

02:14.308 --> 02:15.677
- TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON.

02:15.743 --> 02:17.445
- WELL, I GUESS
I WAS JUST EXPECTING

02:17.545 --> 02:19.514
SOMETHING DIFFERENT,
YOU KNOW.

02:19.580 --> 02:22.050
- CONFESSION?
- [chuckles] WISHFUL THINKING.

02:22.150 --> 02:24.452
[chuckles]
- SID'S GOT YOU WORRIED.

02:24.552 --> 02:26.587
- NO. NO, SID'S NEVER
GOT ME SHOOK.

02:26.688 --> 02:29.724
IT'S--IT'LL BE FINE.

02:30.024 --> 02:32.193
I'LL LEAVE YOU
TO THE SAUCE, OKAY?

02:34.696 --> 02:37.699
- YOU KNOW I'M HERE
IF YOU NEED MY HELP.

02:37.799 --> 02:40.468
- YEAH.
YEAH, I KNOW.

02:47.442 --> 02:50.044
- DID YOU GET
THE CALL OR WHAT?

02:52.280 --> 02:53.414
- WHAT CALL?

02:53.481 --> 02:54.649
- A CALL FROM SID--

02:54.716 --> 02:57.151
IT'S A DIRTY COP WHO WORKS
FOR CARLITO,

02:57.218 --> 02:58.352
THE GUY WHO JUST KILLED SULLA.

02:58.453 --> 03:00.088
THIS GUY YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO BE UNDERCOVER WITH.

03:00.188 --> 03:01.222
- YEAH, MIKE, HE CALLED.

03:01.322 --> 03:02.457
HE SAID WE'D TALK
IN THE MORNING.

03:02.523 --> 03:05.293
- DAMN IT.
IS HE PUTTING YOU OFF?

03:05.359 --> 03:07.361
I NEED TO GO DOWN
TO THE FBI OFFICE IN THE MORNING

03:07.462 --> 03:10.064
AND GIVE THEM A FULL DEBRIEFING
ABOUT WHY FIVE PEOPLE

03:10.131 --> 03:11.799
WERE JUST GUNNED DOWN
IN SYLMAR UNDER MY WATCH,

03:12.066 --> 03:13.334
AND I HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT TO SAY.

03:13.434 --> 03:14.669
- WELL, WHY DON'T YOU SAY

03:14.736 --> 03:16.104
YOU'RE STILL WORKING?
- WORKING.

03:16.204 --> 03:18.339
RIGHT.
WELL, WORKING DOESN'T MEAN SH--.

03:18.439 --> 03:20.108
WORKING JUST MEANS
I HAVEN'T FAILED YET.

03:20.208 --> 03:21.709
- OKAY, MIKE, WELL, TELL
THEM YOU HAVEN'T FAILED YET.

03:22.009 --> 03:23.244
- WE GET CLOSE,

03:23.311 --> 03:25.346
AND THEN
EVERY SOLID LEAD WE HAVE

03:25.413 --> 03:27.215
JUST GETS SWEPT AWAY.

03:29.150 --> 03:33.020
WE NEED TO GET OUR HAND
AROUND SID'S NECK AND SQUEEZE.

03:34.288 --> 03:37.291
WE GOT TO PUT THIS GUY DOWN.

03:47.368 --> 03:48.503
- OH, SO WHAT TIME

03:48.569 --> 03:50.171
ARE WE CHECKING OUT
THE AIRSTRIP TOMORROW?

03:50.238 --> 03:52.774
- I WILL THINK ABOUT THAT
WHEN I WAKE UP IN THE MORNING

03:53.040 --> 03:54.308
AND NOT A MOMENT SOONER.

03:54.375 --> 03:56.444
- LOOK, I WANT TO GET THIS DONE,
AND I NEED TO GET IT DONE NOW.

03:56.511 --> 03:58.746
- JOHNNY, SHH.

04:00.281 --> 04:02.183
- WHAT?
- YOU SMELL THAT?

04:02.250 --> 04:05.219
- I'VE BEEN IN THE CAR
FOR, LIKE, 14 HOU--

04:05.319 --> 04:07.054
- [whispers]
THE SAUCE.

04:07.121 --> 04:09.257
- [inhales deeply]

04:09.323 --> 04:10.591
- YEAH.

04:10.658 --> 04:13.227
- [exhales, whispers]
THANK YOU.

04:13.294 --> 04:15.263
- OH.
- DON'T EVEN THINK ABOUT IT.

04:15.363 --> 04:16.330
I'LL CUT YOU.

04:16.397 --> 04:17.498
- WE DON'T NEED
A MURDER SCENE.

04:17.565 --> 04:19.066
YOU KNOW
THAT WE KNOW THE RULES.

04:19.133 --> 04:21.202
- I KNOW THAT YOU'RE
A SNEAKY LITTLE TOAD

04:21.269 --> 04:22.670
THAT GETS NIGHT HUNGERS.

04:22.737 --> 04:25.473
- YEAH, THAT SMELLS SO GOOD.
- MM-HMM.

04:25.540 --> 04:28.109
- YOU TELL THE STORY YET?
- SAUCE IS BOILING, RIGHT?

04:28.176 --> 04:30.611
- YOU FEEL LIKE
TELLING IT AGAIN?

04:32.246 --> 04:33.381
- FINE.
- MMM!

04:33.447 --> 04:35.049
- OKAY, THING IS, I'VE
BEEN IN THE SAME CLOTHES

04:35.116 --> 04:36.584
FOR, LIKE, 40 HOURS,
SO LET ME GO CHANGE REAL QUICK.

04:36.651 --> 04:37.785
- IT'S A QUICK STORY, BRO.
COME ON.

04:38.085 --> 04:39.387
- LET ME JUST GO CHANGE.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

04:39.453 --> 04:41.389
DON'T START WITHOUT ME.
- I WON'T.

04:41.455 --> 04:43.157
- AH!
[jogging footsteps]

04:44.792 --> 04:46.360
- HE'S HEARD THE STORY
SO MANY TIMES.

04:46.427 --> 04:48.329
YOU CAN START WITHOUT HIM.

05:00.041 --> 05:01.742
- [gasps]
JE--

05:04.011 --> 05:06.147
- WE GOTTA GO TALK, DALE.
- HA HA.

05:06.214 --> 05:08.282
HOW WAS MY TRIP?
MY TRIP WAS LONG.

05:08.349 --> 05:11.285
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

05:11.352 --> 05:13.688
- THIS IS SERIOUS.

05:21.429 --> 05:23.564
[indistinct chatter]

05:23.664 --> 05:26.300
[seagull crying]

05:26.400 --> 05:29.170
- AND YOU'RE ABSOLUTELY SURE
TAPE.

05:29.237 --> 05:32.139
- I AM ABSOLUTELY SURE
TAPE.

05:32.206 --> 05:33.608
- I'M NOT DOING THIS AGAIN.

05:33.708 --> 05:35.309
IF YOU'RE RUNNING,
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN, MAN.

05:35.409 --> 05:36.677
I'M SORRY.
- I'M NOT RUNNING.

05:36.744 --> 05:38.579
- BECAUSE THEY CAME
AT ME HARD LAST TIME.

05:38.679 --> 05:40.281
- I'M NOT RUNNING.

05:40.348 --> 05:42.750
CHARLIE'S WHAT, SIX WEEKS IN?
I CAN'T--I'M STAYING PUT.

05:43.050 --> 05:44.151
- OKAY, SO WHAT ARE
WE TALKING ABOUT?

05:44.218 --> 05:45.586
- I GOT TO GET MY HANDS
ON THAT TAPE

05:45.686 --> 05:47.188
BEFORE HE PLAYS IT
FOR SOMEBODY ELSE.

05:47.288 --> 05:48.456
- HE?

05:48.522 --> 05:49.457
WHO HAS IT?

05:49.557 --> 05:51.225
- SID.

05:51.325 --> 05:53.361
- YOUR SID?
- IT'S GOT TO BE.

05:53.461 --> 05:55.363
CALL CAME THROUGH
ON MY GTF COVER PHONE.

05:55.463 --> 05:57.198
- JESUS CHRIST.
WHAT THE HELL DOES HE WANT?

05:57.265 --> 05:58.532
- THAT'S A GOOD QUESTION.

05:58.599 --> 05:59.600
I TELL YOU WHAT--
AFTER THE TAPE,

05:59.700 --> 06:01.202
HE CALLED
FOUR TIMES LAST NIGHT.

06:01.302 --> 06:03.137
- WHAT, YOU DIDN'T PICK UP?

06:03.204 --> 06:04.472
- THE KIND OF CONVERSATION
I'D RATHER HAVE

06:04.538 --> 06:05.806
WHEN I'M LOOKING
IN THE MAN'S EYES.

06:06.073 --> 06:10.578
- SOUNDS LIKE YOU WANT TO TAKE
ANOTHER TRIP TO THE DESERT.

06:10.645 --> 06:13.247
BRIGGS, SID HAS A CREW.

06:13.347 --> 06:15.549
IF SID KNOWS,
HIS CREW PROBABLY KNOWS.

06:15.616 --> 06:17.652
SO HOW MANY TRIPS TO THE DESERT
ARE YOU GONNA TAKE?

06:17.752 --> 06:19.453
- I DON'T NEED THEM, OKAY?

06:19.520 --> 06:21.055
I NEED THAT TAPE.

06:21.122 --> 06:22.323
IF THEY GOT NO EVIDENCE,

06:22.390 --> 06:23.691
THEY CAN'T PROVE
ANYTHING, RIGHT?

06:23.758 --> 06:25.192
ARE YOU GONNA HELP ME, DALE?

06:25.259 --> 06:28.029
- YOU'RE AN ASSHOLE.
YOU KNOW THAT?

06:28.095 --> 06:29.597
YOU KNOW AS WELL AS I DO,
IF THEY GET YOU,

06:29.664 --> 06:31.332
THEY'RE GONNA COME GUNNING
FOR ME NEXT.

06:31.399 --> 06:34.368
SO WHAT CHOICE DO I HAVE?

06:34.435 --> 06:36.671
DON'T WASTE MY TIME.
WHAT DO YOU NEED?

06:36.771 --> 06:38.739
- AN ALIBI.

06:38.806 --> 06:40.474
THERE'S A PLACE AROUND
THE CORNER FROM HERE

06:40.541 --> 06:42.076
CALLED NANCY'S--
A LITTLE DINER.

06:42.143 --> 06:46.213
PLEASE, GO THERE,
ORDER TWO BREAKFASTS ON ME.

06:46.280 --> 06:49.417
THAT'S IT.

06:49.483 --> 06:52.520
- I'M TIRED, BRIGGS.

06:52.620 --> 06:54.155
- ME TOO.

06:54.255 --> 06:56.757
I HAVEN'T SLEPT
IN DAYS, JAKES.

06:58.793 --> 07:03.030
- WE NEED TO GET OUR HAND
AROUND SID'S NECK AND SQUEEZE.

07:03.130 --> 07:06.400
[rock music]

07:06.467 --> 07:14.375
♪ ♪

07:55.182 --> 07:58.119
[electronic music]

07:58.185 --> 08:04.125
♪ ♪

08:09.130 --> 08:10.231
[doorbell rings]

08:16.070 --> 08:17.538
- PAUL.

08:21.776 --> 08:24.011
I CALLED YOU LAST NIGHT
REPEATEDLY.

08:24.078 --> 08:25.646
- THAT'S WHY I'M HERE.

08:25.713 --> 08:28.115
- YEAH? COFFEE?
I GOT TO TURN MY BRAIN ON.

08:33.621 --> 08:36.624
YOU JUST MISSED THE WIFE
TAKING PATRICK TO SCHOOL.

08:36.724 --> 08:38.059
HE LOVES IT.
HE LOVES SCHOOL.

08:38.125 --> 08:40.194
YOU SHOULD HEAR HIM GOING OFF
ABOUT DINOSAURS.

08:40.294 --> 08:42.029
HOLD THAT.
THIS GUY RIGHT OVER HERE--

08:42.096 --> 08:44.598
HIS TREE SH--S ALL OVER
EVERYTHING.

08:44.698 --> 08:46.200
- AH.
- EVERYWHERE.

08:46.300 --> 08:48.569
I ASKED HIM TO CUT IT DOWN,
DIDN'T I?

08:48.636 --> 08:51.172
- HEY, UH, SID,
I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT,

08:51.238 --> 08:52.473
BUT, YOU KNOW,
I REALLY DIDN'T DRIVE

08:52.573 --> 08:55.176
ALL THE WAY OUT HERE
TO TALK ABOUT YOUR DIRTY POOL.

08:55.276 --> 08:58.179
WHAT'S GOING ON?

08:58.279 --> 09:00.748
- AH...
[exhales]

09:01.015 --> 09:02.783
OKAY.

09:03.084 --> 09:06.487
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I OWE YOU SOME ANSWERS.

09:06.554 --> 09:08.389
WHAT HAPPENED IN THERE?

09:10.424 --> 09:12.493
ALL RIGHT, I GOTTA
TAKE YOU WAY BACK HERE, MAN.

09:12.593 --> 09:14.795
20 YEARS AGO,
I MAKE DETECTIVE.

09:15.096 --> 09:18.099
CARLOS SOLANO'S RUNNING
A SMALL CREW BACK THEN.

09:18.165 --> 09:19.500
I BUST HIM
ON A NARCOTICS BEEF.

09:19.600 --> 09:20.568
HE GETS TEN YEARS.

09:20.634 --> 09:22.670
BUT THERE'S
SOMETHING ABOUT HIM.

09:22.770 --> 09:24.672
I DON'T KNOW. I LIKE THE GUY.
- RIGHT.

09:24.772 --> 09:25.806
- HE WANTS TO SEE ME.

09:26.107 --> 09:27.141
HE HANDS ME A BROCHURE

09:27.241 --> 09:29.643
FOR THE PRISON
EQUESTRIAN PROGRAM...

09:29.743 --> 09:31.779
HORSES FOR CONVICTS.

09:32.079 --> 09:33.581
- [chuckles]
- [laughs]

09:33.647 --> 09:35.516
SO I SAY,
"OKAY, YOU WANT YOUR PONIES?

09:35.616 --> 09:37.151
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA GIVE ME?"

09:37.218 --> 09:38.752
HE STARTS GIVING ME INFO
ON OTHER CREWS.

09:39.053 --> 09:41.088
I START MAKING
THE BIGGEST BUSTS OF MY CAREER.

09:41.155 --> 09:43.124
MY NAME IS NOW ON THE MAP.

09:43.190 --> 09:44.792
- AND KNOCKING OFF
HIS COMPETITION, RIGHT?

09:45.059 --> 09:47.094
- THIS IS TRUE.
- [chuckles]

09:47.161 --> 09:48.295
- BUT HE GETS OUT.

09:48.395 --> 09:49.663
THE ARRANGEMENT CONTINUES.

09:49.730 --> 09:52.433
THEN HE GOES
AND DOES SOMETHING STUPID.

09:52.533 --> 09:54.435
HE PUTS ONE OF HIS PARTNERS
IN THE GROUND.

09:54.535 --> 09:56.604
- I THOUGHT THAT WAS
PAR FOR THE COURSE, YOU KNOW.

09:56.670 --> 09:59.273
- SURE, BUT WHAT WAS STUPID
WAS THAT HE THOUGHT

09:59.340 --> 10:02.243
I WOULD LET THAT SLIDE.

10:02.309 --> 10:03.744
- JUST LIKE
YOU COULDN'T LET HIM SLIDE

10:04.011 --> 10:07.281
ON RUNNING THOSE GIRLS
OUT OF SYLMAR?

10:07.381 --> 10:11.285
- I HAD TO SMACK HIM DOWN.
- IT WAS NECESSARY, HUH?

10:11.385 --> 10:14.255
- I GOTTA LET CARLOS SOLANO
KNOW WHERE THE LINE IS.

10:14.355 --> 10:17.024
YOU'D DO THE SAME THING.

10:18.526 --> 10:20.427
- ABSOLUTELY.

10:20.528 --> 10:22.530
- YOU LOOK LIKE
YOU NEED SOME SLEEP, PAUL.

10:22.596 --> 10:24.732
- [chuckles]
YEAH.

10:27.434 --> 10:30.704
- THIS PLACE
BURNED BECAUSE OF US.

10:30.804 --> 10:34.675
- WE NEED TO GET OUR HAND
AROUND SID'S NECK AND SQUEEZE.

10:42.550 --> 10:44.185
- HOW WAS NANCY'S?

10:44.285 --> 10:46.387
- IF ANYBODY ASKS,
THE EGGS WERE RUNNY.

10:46.453 --> 10:48.489
ARE WE DONE?
MAY I GO HOME?

10:48.556 --> 10:50.491
- SID DOESN'T HAVE THE TAPE.

10:50.558 --> 10:51.759
- HOW DO YOU KNOW?

10:52.026 --> 10:53.761
- BECAUSE IF I'M SID
AND I PLAYED MY ONLY HAND

10:54.028 --> 10:55.329
WHEN I PLAYED THAT TAPE,
I DON'T SHOW UP

10:55.429 --> 10:57.164
TO THE FRONT DOOR
WEARING A SMILE.

10:57.231 --> 10:58.365
I SHOW UP WEARING KEVLAR.

10:58.432 --> 11:00.034
IT WASN'T HIM.
- OKAY, SO MAYBE

11:00.100 --> 11:02.436
IT'S ONE OF HIS CRONIES--
ARCHIE, MARTINEZ.

11:04.238 --> 11:06.040
- IT'S MIKE.

11:06.340 --> 11:08.242
MIKE?
- YEAH.

11:08.309 --> 11:10.010
- BRIGGS, YOU'RE
OUT OF YOUR GODDAMN MIND.

11:10.077 --> 11:11.745
FIRST OFF,
HOW WOULD HE GET THE TAPE?

11:12.046 --> 11:14.315
SECOND, IF IT WAS WARREN,
YOU'D BE IN HANDCUFFS YESTERDAY.

11:14.415 --> 11:17.318
- MM-HMM.
EXCEPT I'M STILL USEFUL TO HIM.

11:17.418 --> 11:19.186
YOU KNOW, TWO MINUTES
AFTER I GOT THAT CALL,

11:19.253 --> 11:20.621
I HAD MIKE STARING ME
IN THE FACE,

11:20.721 --> 11:22.389
SAYING WE GOTTA
PUT SID DOWN.

11:22.456 --> 11:24.592
- YOU THINK MIKE
WANTS YOU TO KILL SID?

11:24.692 --> 11:27.595
- IT DAMN NEAR WORKED.

11:27.661 --> 11:29.363
- I DON'T KNOW, BRIGGS.
- LOOK...

11:29.463 --> 11:32.132
MIKE IS TIRED
OF GETTING GOT, OKAY?

11:32.199 --> 11:33.801
HE'S LOOKING
FOR ANY WAY TO END THIS.

11:34.068 --> 11:36.270
IF I PUT SID 6 FEET
UNDER THE EARTH, GUESS WHAT.

11:36.337 --> 11:38.472
MIKE'S GOT ME DEAD TO RIGHTS
ON TWO MURDERS.

11:38.572 --> 11:40.241
TWO, D.J., OKAY?

11:40.341 --> 11:41.508
NO SID, NO BRIGGS.

11:41.575 --> 11:45.212
- YOU EVER THINK
IT MIGHT BE TIME TO JUST...

11:45.312 --> 11:48.382
GET OUT IN FRONT OF THIS,
COME CLEAN?

11:48.482 --> 11:50.784
- THERE'S STILL TIME.
- YEAH, UNTIL THERE ISN'T.

11:51.085 --> 11:52.653
- HEY, LOOK, MAN,
IF HE'S PLAYING THE TAPE FOR ME,

11:52.753 --> 11:54.421
HE'S NOT PLAYING IT
FOR HIS BOSSES IN D.C.

11:54.488 --> 11:55.723
THAT'S FOR DAMN SURE.

11:55.789 --> 11:57.658
AS LONG AS HE THINKS I'M LOOKING
AT SID, I CAN STOP HIM.

11:57.758 --> 11:59.393
- STOP HIM HOW?

12:02.229 --> 12:03.430
GOD DAMN IT, BRIGGS.

12:03.497 --> 12:07.768
- LOOK, MAN, I WILL SEE
MY CHILD GROW UP, JAKES.

12:08.035 --> 12:10.204
- OKAY.

12:10.271 --> 12:13.774
NO MORE ALIBIS.

12:14.041 --> 12:17.244
I'M DONE.

12:17.344 --> 12:20.447
- D.J.
- ENOUGH.

12:20.514 --> 12:22.283
MY BED IS CALLIN'.

12:34.428 --> 12:36.463
[man shouts, voice echoes]

12:41.101 --> 12:45.039
YOU, ME, FOREVER.

12:45.139 --> 12:46.240
- YO. WHERE THE HELL...
- NO.

12:46.307 --> 12:47.474
YOU BEEN AT, MAN?
- NO!

12:47.541 --> 12:49.376
I NEED YOUR HELP.
- IS THERE A SIGN ON MY FACE

12:49.443 --> 12:50.678
SAYING I GIVE A SH--?

12:50.778 --> 12:53.380
BECAUSE EVERYBODY KEEPS COMING
TO ME WITH THEIR PROBLEMS.

12:53.480 --> 12:56.016
I DON'T GIVE A SH--.
SO, PLEASE, JUST GET OUT.

12:56.116 --> 12:58.185
- ICE STILL HAS THAT SATELLITE
OFFICE IN MEXICO, RIGHT--

12:58.252 --> 12:59.687
THE ONE THAT DEALS
WITH FOREIGN OPS?

12:59.787 --> 13:01.121
- SO WHAT?

13:01.188 --> 13:02.523
- I NEED YOU TO GET IN TOUCH
WITH SOMEBODY THERE.

13:02.589 --> 13:03.757
I GOT TO GET LUCIA OUT.

13:04.024 --> 13:07.227
- [laughs] YOU WANT ICE
TO EXFILTRATE YOUR GIRLFRIEND?

13:07.294 --> 13:08.662
- YEAH.

13:08.762 --> 13:10.164
- NO.
- YEAH.

13:10.230 --> 13:12.399
SHE'S IN TROUBLE DOWN THERE.
- NO SH--.

13:12.466 --> 13:14.468
I'VE BEEN SAYING FOR WEEKS,
IF YOU DO THIS,

13:14.568 --> 13:15.669
BAD THINGS WILL HAPPEN.

13:15.736 --> 13:18.505
SO WHAT ELEMENT HERE
IS SURPRISING YOU?

13:18.572 --> 13:20.341
- YOU'RE NOT GONNA HELP ME?
- MM-MM.

13:20.441 --> 13:23.310
- ALL RIGHT, I'LL GO ASK MIKE.
- YOU CAN'T TELL MIKE.

13:23.410 --> 13:26.013
- I CAN TELL MIKE, OKAY?
HE KNOWS SHE'S NOT INVOLVED.

13:26.113 --> 13:28.082
HE'LL UNDERSTAND.
HE'LL PROTECT HER.

13:28.148 --> 13:29.583
- "HE'LL UNDERSTAND"?
- YEAH.

13:29.683 --> 13:32.386
- LET ME TELL YOU
WHAT HE'LL UNDERSTAND.

13:32.453 --> 13:35.155
HE'LL UNDERSTAND THAT THE MOMENT
YOU SQUIRMED UP

13:35.255 --> 13:37.691
INTO MISS CARTEL MEXICO
PRINCESS,

13:37.758 --> 13:39.426
YOUR COVER BECAME
A CONFLICT OF INTEREST.

13:39.526 --> 13:42.730
HE'LL UNDERSTAND THAT YOU'RE
NO LONGER A CREDIBLE WITNESS,

13:43.030 --> 13:45.199
THAT YOU PROBABLY CAN'T TAKE
THE STAND IF WE INDICT,

13:45.299 --> 13:48.369
AND THAT THERE'S A GOOD CHANCE
YOU SCREWED UP HIS WHOLE CASE,

13:48.435 --> 13:49.570
NOT JUST THE GIRL.

13:51.805 --> 13:53.374
- I CAN'T JUST LEAVE HER
DOWN THERE.

13:53.474 --> 13:55.042
- YOU CAN.

13:55.109 --> 13:57.378
THAT'S THE ONLY THING
YOU CAN DO.

13:57.444 --> 13:58.746
- I TOLD HER
I'D COME BACK FOR HER.

13:59.046 --> 14:00.681
- YOU LIED.

14:00.748 --> 14:03.183
YOU LIE FOR A LIVING.

14:08.489 --> 14:10.190
[door closes]
AAH!

14:16.497 --> 14:18.098
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

14:18.198 --> 14:20.200
- THE BALLERINA
DIDN'T USED TO SPIN.

14:20.300 --> 14:22.536
NOW IT DOES.

14:22.603 --> 14:26.140
- IF IT'S FIXED,
WHY ARE YOU TAKING IT APART?

14:26.206 --> 14:28.442
- BECAUSE I LIKED IT BETTER
WHEN IT WAS BROKEN.

14:31.311 --> 14:33.313
WHAT'S UP?

14:33.380 --> 14:35.382
- I WANTED TO SAY THANK YOU.

14:35.482 --> 14:36.617
- FOR WHAT?

14:36.717 --> 14:39.753
- FOR SAVING MY LIFE WITH SID.

14:40.053 --> 14:43.257
- WELL, YOU WOULD HAVE DONE
THE SAME FOR ME.

14:45.058 --> 14:46.760
- HE WOULD'VE KILLED ME.

14:47.060 --> 14:49.763
- WELL, WE USED TO HAVE
SOMETHING SPECIAL.

14:50.063 --> 14:51.765
- RIGHT.

14:55.769 --> 14:58.038
IT'S CRAZY.

14:58.105 --> 15:00.374
AS TERRIBLE AS THE LAST
COUPLE DAYS HAVE BEEN--

15:00.474 --> 15:03.777
FIVE PEOPLE ARE DEAD,
YOU KNOW--

15:04.077 --> 15:05.579
A HELL OF A LOT'S
GOTTEN ACCOMPLISHED.

15:05.646 --> 15:08.215
CARLOS SOLANO MOVED OFF
HIS SON'S CRUISE-SHIP IDEA.

15:08.315 --> 15:10.517
BRIGGS INCHED CLOSER TO SID.

15:10.617 --> 15:12.786
YOU GOT YOUR GIRLS.

15:13.086 --> 15:15.456
I THINK THEY CALL
THAT A TRIFECTA.

15:15.522 --> 15:17.524
- WE SHOULD COUNT
OUR BLESSINGS.

15:17.591 --> 15:19.026
- THERE'LL BE
AN INVESTIGATION, YOU KNOW.

15:19.126 --> 15:20.527
- BUT THAT'S REALLY HARD TO DO
WITH LINA STILL MISSING.

15:20.627 --> 15:21.795
- WE'LL LOOK INTO THAT TOO.

15:22.095 --> 15:25.599
- I WAS THINKING ABOUT WRITING
HER PARENTS A LETTER.

15:25.666 --> 15:28.769
YOU WANT TO HELP ME
WITH THAT?

15:29.036 --> 15:30.504
- ABSOLUTELY.

15:30.571 --> 15:33.173
- I'LL SEE YOU DOWNSTAIRS
AT DINNER.

15:47.421 --> 15:49.790
- CAN I GET A 20 ON EDDIE?
BELLA'S LOOKING FOR HIM.

15:50.057 --> 15:51.425
- YEAH, I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

15:51.525 --> 15:52.593
- UM, EXCUSE ME, BROTHER.

15:52.659 --> 15:54.361
ARE YOU THE LOCATIONS MANAGER
FOR THIS FILM?

15:54.428 --> 15:56.663
- YEAH, CAN I HELP YOU?
- YEAH, PAUL WEST, LAPD.

15:56.730 --> 15:59.132
HOW LONG YOU GUYS SHOOTING HERE?
- THE NEXT FOUR NIGHTS.

15:59.199 --> 16:02.202
- AH. YEAH, THAT'S, UH--
THAT'S GONNA BE A PROBLEM.

16:02.302 --> 16:04.171
THERE'S BEEN A MIX-UP DOWNTOWN.

16:04.238 --> 16:06.440
SANITATION'S RUNNING PIPE HERE
THE NEXT COUPLE OF NIGHTS.

16:06.540 --> 16:08.175
LOOKS LIKE YOU GUYS ARE
PROBABLY GONNA HAVE TO MOVE.

16:08.275 --> 16:10.010
- WE HAVE PERMITS.

16:10.110 --> 16:11.278
THIS IS BULLSH--.

16:11.345 --> 16:13.614
- LISTEN, MAN,
I'M JUST THE MESSENGER, OKAY?

16:13.680 --> 16:15.549
PLEASE DON'T MAKE MY LIFE
ANY HARDER.

16:15.649 --> 16:17.718
LOOK, I MADE A COUPLE OF CALLS
ON YOUR BEHALF.

16:18.018 --> 16:19.586
WE CAN OFFER YOU A COUPLE
OF BLOCKS JUST DOWN THE WAY,

16:19.686 --> 16:21.688
BEAUTIFUL SPOT RIGHT IN FRONT
OF GETTY NATIONAL BANK.

16:21.755 --> 16:23.156
- IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE.

16:23.257 --> 16:24.458
- IT'S GONNA HAVE TO BE,
MY FRIEND,

16:24.558 --> 16:26.159
BECAUSE LOOK, EITHER
YOU'RE GONNA SHARE REAL ESTATE

16:26.226 --> 16:27.427
WITH SANITATION,

16:27.494 --> 16:29.763
OR YOU'RE GONNA PICK UP STAKES
VAMONOS.

16:30.030 --> 16:31.798
WHAT'S IT GONNA BE?

16:32.065 --> 16:35.302
[folksy blues song]

16:35.402 --> 16:43.410
♪ ♪

16:59.326 --> 17:02.095
- HEY, BRIGGS IS HERE.
WE CAN START.

17:06.567 --> 17:08.168
- WATCH IT.
WATCH IT.

17:08.235 --> 17:10.103
- ABOUT TIME. ABOUT TIME.
- LET'S DO IT.

17:10.203 --> 17:12.472
- I COULD EAT MY OWN HAND.
- ALL RIGHT.

17:12.539 --> 17:13.607
- OH, NO.

17:13.674 --> 17:15.242
- VOILA.
- YES!

17:15.309 --> 17:17.311
GET INTO MY BODY.
I'M STARVING.

17:17.377 --> 17:19.079
- THANK YOU, CHARLIE.

17:19.179 --> 17:20.480
- I GUESS
THIS WOULDN'T BE SAUCE NIGHT

17:20.547 --> 17:22.316
WITHOUT A BRIEF TOAST.

17:22.382 --> 17:24.351
I KNOW EVERYBODY'S HUNGRY,
SO I'LL KEEP IT SHORT.

17:24.451 --> 17:25.452
TO GRACELAND.

17:25.519 --> 17:27.387
- YEAH, WORD UP.
- TO HOME.

17:27.487 --> 17:28.388
- HOME.
- CHEERS.

17:28.488 --> 17:29.489
- CHEERS.
- CHEERS.

17:29.590 --> 17:30.591
- WELCOME HOME.

17:30.657 --> 17:32.326
- NOW LET'S EAT.
MANGIA.

17:32.392 --> 17:33.460
- LADIES FIRST.

17:33.527 --> 17:35.395
PAIGE, YOU HUNGRY?
- I'M ALWAYS HUNGRY.

17:35.495 --> 17:39.032
[cell phone chiming]

17:39.099 --> 17:41.068
- Y-YO!
- NO PHONES ON SAUCE NIGHT.

17:41.134 --> 17:44.037
- THAT WAS WORK.
- I DON'T CARE. SAUCE TIME.

17:44.104 --> 17:47.040
- HEY, JOHNNY,
WAS THAT LUCIA OR CARLITO?

17:47.107 --> 17:49.076
- UM, CARLITO.

17:49.142 --> 17:50.744
- THAT MUST'VE BEEN CRAZY.

17:51.044 --> 17:52.446
- WHAT?

17:52.512 --> 17:56.550
- WHEN SID CALLED AND TIPPED OFF
CARLITO'S LITTLE SIDE PROJECT.

17:56.617 --> 17:58.719
- ACTUALLY, THE TIMING
COULDN'T HAVE BEEN MORE PERFECT.

17:58.785 --> 17:59.753
- HOW SO?

18:00.053 --> 18:02.389
- NO WORK TALK--
SAUCE NIGHT.

18:02.456 --> 18:05.659
- NO. IF MIKE WANTS
TO TALK WORK, LET'S TALK WORK.

18:05.726 --> 18:07.394
- NO, YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU'RE RIGHT, CHUCK.

18:07.494 --> 18:09.663
WE GET SO WRAPPED UP
IN WORK SOMETIMES.

18:09.730 --> 18:11.064
WELL, WHAT'S GOING ON?

18:11.131 --> 18:12.799
DOES ANYBODY GOT ANYTHING
GOING ON IN THEIR LIVES

18:13.066 --> 18:14.735
THEY WANT TO SHARE?

18:19.106 --> 18:21.208
- ANYBODY ELSE HAVING, UH,
TROUBLE WITH THE WASHER?

18:21.274 --> 18:23.243
- YEAH, YOU JUST HAVE TO TURN
THE LITTLE KNOB TO THE LEFT

18:23.343 --> 18:24.578
UNTIL IT CLICKS.
- OH, OKAY.

18:24.645 --> 18:26.380
IT'S A KNOB THING?
'CAUSE I WAS GONNA FIX IT.

18:26.446 --> 18:28.248
- IT'LL CLICK.

18:28.315 --> 18:31.151
- IN LIEU OF THAT
STIMULATING CONVERSATION,

18:31.251 --> 18:32.386
I GUESS WORK IT IS.

18:32.486 --> 18:34.054
SORRY, CHUCK.

18:34.121 --> 18:35.622
JOHNNY, WHY WAS THE TIMING
SO PERFECT?

18:35.689 --> 18:38.792
- WELL, BRIGGS
HAD JUST CALLED ME.

18:39.059 --> 18:41.028
AND I TOLD HIM
THAT CARLOS WASN'T GONNA BUY

18:41.128 --> 18:42.562
INTO THE PLANE IDEA

18:42.663 --> 18:45.365
UNLESS WE FOUND A WAY
TO DISCREDIT CARLITO, SO...

18:45.432 --> 18:48.502
IT WAS JUST PERFECT.
RIGHT, BRIGGS?

18:48.568 --> 18:51.705
- WHAT'S THE MATTER, BRIGGS?
YOU SEEM A LITTLE OUT OF IT.

18:51.805 --> 18:54.374
- I HAVEN'T SLEPT.

18:54.441 --> 18:56.743
- JOHNNY, WHEN I CATCH SID

18:57.010 --> 18:59.012
AND ASK HIM
WHO TIPPED HIM OFF TO ALL THIS,

18:59.112 --> 19:01.081
WHAT DO YOU THINK
HE'S GONNA SAY?

19:01.148 --> 19:02.549
- YOU KNOW, I THINK SID
WOULD PROBABLY

19:02.616 --> 19:04.651
PRETTY MUCH SAY ANYTHING
TO SHAVE A SINGLE DAY

19:04.718 --> 19:06.153
OFF OF A LIFE SENTENCE.

19:06.253 --> 19:07.587
BUT YOU KNOW
WHAT'S FUNNY, MIKE?

19:07.688 --> 19:09.623
I GET THE IMPRESSION
THAT YOU WOULD NOT BE HAPPY

19:09.690 --> 19:13.293
UNLESS SID SPENDS THE REST
OF HIS DAYS IN THE GROUND.

19:13.393 --> 19:14.594
WHY DON'T YOU SHARE
WITH EVERYBODY

19:14.695 --> 19:15.762
WHAT YOU TOLD ME
LAST NIGHT, MIKE?

19:16.029 --> 19:18.065
I CAN QUOTE YOU.
- THAT'S ENOUGH, BRIGGS.

19:18.165 --> 19:21.034
YOU'RE TIRED.
YOU'RE NOT THINKING CLEARLY.

19:21.134 --> 19:22.736
- WHAT?
COME ON, BABY.

19:23.036 --> 19:25.472
- NO ONE WANTS TO HEAR IT.
- OKAY. I'M SORRY.

19:25.572 --> 19:27.140
I APOLOGIZE.

19:27.207 --> 19:28.575
I THOUGHT THIS WAS
WHAT YOU WANTED--

19:28.675 --> 19:33.313
YOU KNOW, EVERYBODY TO COME
TOGETHER AND SHARE STUFF

19:33.380 --> 19:35.415
AND BE HONEST ABOUT SH--.

19:35.482 --> 19:37.350
- YOU'RE NOT HONEST
WITH ANYBODY.

19:37.451 --> 19:38.719
- OKAY.

19:39.019 --> 19:41.221
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU SHOW ME
WHAT THAT LOOKS LIKE, BABE?

19:41.321 --> 19:42.456
I HAVE AN IDEA.

19:42.556 --> 19:44.324
WHY DON'T WE START TALKING
ABOUT KELLY BADILLO?

19:44.424 --> 19:45.659
- DID YOU JUST SAY
"KELLY BADILLO"?

19:45.726 --> 19:47.594
- YOU PIECE OF SH--.
- EASY, MAMA BEAR.

19:47.694 --> 19:49.629
- WHAT DID YOU CALL ME?
- YES, BUT--

19:49.730 --> 19:53.600
[overlapping shouting]

19:58.605 --> 20:01.374
- TELL ME THIS!
HOW FAR WILL YOU GO TO GET SID?

20:01.475 --> 20:02.642
- I THINK
THE BETTER QUESTION IS,

20:02.709 --> 20:04.177
WHAT WOULDN'T I DO
TO CATCH YOU?

20:04.244 --> 20:05.445
- COME GET IT, YOUNG MAN.

20:05.512 --> 20:08.348
[all shouting]

20:08.415 --> 20:09.750
- WHAT DO YOU THINK OF THAT?
ALL RIGHT?

20:10.050 --> 20:12.786
[opera music in background]

20:13.086 --> 20:14.788
♪ ♪

20:15.088 --> 20:17.491
- I'M IN LOVE WITH LUCIA.
- JOHNNY.

20:17.557 --> 20:20.594
- I'VE BEEN SLEEPING WITH HER
THIS WHOLE TIME.

20:23.363 --> 20:26.333
[cell phone ringing]

20:30.237 --> 20:32.239
- [sighs]

20:32.339 --> 20:34.074
[cell phone beeps]
WHAT'S UP?

20:34.141 --> 20:36.409
- WE GOT A PROBLEM.
- WHAT KIND OF PROBLEM?

20:36.476 --> 20:39.746
- SOME SH-- ASS SLASHER FLICK
IS WORKING NIGHTS ON OUR BLOCK.

20:40.046 --> 20:41.348
IT MEANS WE'RE LOOKING
AT CROWDS,

20:41.448 --> 20:43.250
LIGHTS,
AND POLICE ESCORTS.

20:43.350 --> 20:45.051
- JESUS CHRIST.

20:45.118 --> 20:46.052
WHAT NOW?

20:46.119 --> 20:47.487
- NOW?
NOW NOTHING.

20:47.587 --> 20:50.791
WE CAN'T WORK
UNDER THAT KIND OF EXPOSURE.

20:51.091 --> 20:52.125
JOB'S OFF.

20:52.225 --> 20:53.426
[line clicks, dial tone]

20:53.527 --> 20:56.163
[opera continues]

21:05.105 --> 21:06.139
- YOU KNOW WHAT
THIS PLACE IS?

21:06.239 --> 21:08.508
- I KNOW EXACTLY
WHAT THIS PLACE IS.

21:08.575 --> 21:12.112
YOU KILLED EVERYONE HERE.
[echoing]

21:12.179 --> 21:14.514
- WHAT THE HELL'S HER PROBLEM?

21:14.614 --> 21:16.116
WHY DOESN'T SHE WANT
TO GO THROUGH WITH IT?

21:16.183 --> 21:17.517
- THERE'S A FILM SHOOTING
RIGHT ACROSS THE STREET

21:17.617 --> 21:19.386
THE NIGHT OF THE HEIST.
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

21:19.486 --> 21:21.121
- "JOHN WOODSMAN VII"
OR SOMETHING.

21:21.221 --> 21:22.255
- WHAT IS THAT, A PORNO?

21:22.489 --> 21:23.657
WOODSMAN JOHN VII?

21:23.757 --> 21:25.158
NO, THAT AIN'T NO PORNO.

21:25.258 --> 21:27.394
HE'S THIS LUMBERJACK
WHO COMES BACK FROM THE DEAD

21:27.494 --> 21:29.429
TO CHOP DOWN
SLUTTY TEENAGERS.

21:29.496 --> 21:31.031
- YOU'RE LIKE THE WIKIPEDIA
OF NONSENSE.

21:31.097 --> 21:32.432
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
- IT'S A PRETTY GOOD MOVIE.

21:32.532 --> 21:34.167
- ALL RIGHT, LISTEN,
CAN WE TALK SOLUTIONS?

21:34.234 --> 21:36.703
EVERY GODDAMN TIME WE GET
THIS CLOSE, SOMETHING HAPPENS.

21:36.770 --> 21:39.306
WELL, NOT THIS TIME, OKAY?

21:39.372 --> 21:41.741
- IS THERE A POSSIBILITY THAT
WE CAN DO IT IN A DAY OR TWO?

21:42.008 --> 21:44.411
- NO. THEY CHANGE
THE SECURITY CODE EVERY NIGHT.

21:44.477 --> 21:46.680
AMBER SPENT WEEKS ON
DIGITAL RECON FINDING A MATCH.

21:46.746 --> 21:48.548
IF YOU WANT TO WAIT
A FEW MORE WEEKS, BUT--

21:48.648 --> 21:50.016
- I MEAN, THE AIRDROP'S
IN THREE OR FOUR DAYS.

21:50.116 --> 21:52.385
- WE HAVE TO DO THE HEIST,
AND WE HAVE TO DO IT NOW.

21:55.088 --> 21:58.291
- THEN DO IT DURING THE DAY.

21:58.391 --> 22:00.560
THE DOORS ARE WIDE OPEN, NO NEED
FOR SECURITY CODES, RIGHT?

22:00.660 --> 22:02.028
- YEAH, BUT THEN
YOU GOT TO WORRY

22:02.095 --> 22:03.263
ABOUT CIVILIANS
AND SECURITY.

22:03.330 --> 22:06.299
WE NEED A WHOLE TEAM FOR THAT.
- HMM.

22:06.366 --> 22:07.701
- WE COULD BE THAT TEAM.

22:07.767 --> 22:10.470
- OKAY, NOW YOU'RE STEPPING
INTO ILLEGAL TERRITORY, MIKE.

22:10.570 --> 22:12.739
- YEAH, BUT IF WE'RE THE ONES
WATCHING THE HOSTAGES,

22:13.039 --> 22:14.074
THEY'LL BE SAFE, RIGHT?

22:14.174 --> 22:15.675
WE COULD EVEN TELL
THEM WE'RE FEDS.

22:15.742 --> 22:17.344
- YOU GONNA GET FBI APPROVAL
ON THAT?

22:17.444 --> 22:18.745
- WELL, AS LONG AS
WE GET OUR PERP,

22:19.045 --> 22:20.614
THEY'LL LET US DO
PRETTY MUCH ANYTHING WE WANT.

22:20.714 --> 22:22.015
RIGHT, MIKE?

22:22.082 --> 22:23.683
- I DON'T THINK AMBER'S
GONNA GO FOR THAT.

22:23.750 --> 22:25.685
I PROBABLY GOT A BETTER SHOT
OF HER GOING TO SEE

22:25.752 --> 22:27.487
"BIG JOHNSON 19" OR SOMETHING.

22:27.587 --> 22:29.422
- SOMETHING TELLS ME
SHE WOULDN'T LIKE THAT MOVIE.

22:29.489 --> 22:32.192
- YOU GOT TO MAKE HER GO FOR IT.
THAT'S YOUR JOB.

22:32.259 --> 22:33.493
- YOU WANT US TO PLAY
A TEAM OF BANK ROBBERS?

22:33.593 --> 22:34.728
WE CAN'T EVEN GET
THROUGH A DINNER.

22:34.794 --> 22:36.062
- ALL RIGHT, WERE PROFESSIONALS.

22:36.162 --> 22:37.430
WE SHOULD BE ABLE
TO PUT ASIDE

22:37.497 --> 22:39.699
OUR PERSONAL DIFFERENCES
AND GET TO WORK, RIGHT?

22:39.766 --> 22:41.368
- RIGHT.
- YEAH.

22:41.468 --> 22:44.037
- ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.
- [clears throat]

22:50.110 --> 22:52.312
- I DON'T WANT BRIGGS ON THIS.
- ME NEITHER.

22:52.379 --> 22:53.747
HE'S ACTING STRANGE.

22:54.047 --> 22:55.415
- WHEN YOU TALK TO AMBER,
JUST MAKE SURE

22:55.482 --> 22:56.750
SHE DOESN'T NEED
ALL OF US, OKAY?

22:57.017 --> 22:58.184
- OKAY.

23:03.523 --> 23:06.593
CARE TO TRY THE BEST MARINARA
THIS SIDE OF THE ATLANTIC?

23:06.660 --> 23:09.596
[rock music on radio]

23:09.663 --> 23:16.369
♪ ♪

23:16.469 --> 23:17.604
- OH, MY GOD.

23:17.671 --> 23:19.272
- WHAT?
- THIS IS SO GOOD.

23:19.372 --> 23:20.607
- YEAH? THANKS.

23:20.674 --> 23:22.709
- I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'VE BEEN HOLDING OUT ON ME.

23:22.776 --> 23:27.380
- YEAH, WELL, IT DOESN'T HAVE
TO END, YOU KNOW.

23:27.480 --> 23:29.582
- I DON'T RISK MY LIFE
FOR PUSSY.

23:29.649 --> 23:31.484
- GOOD, 'CAUSE THAT'S NOT
WHAT I WAS OFFERING.

23:31.584 --> 23:34.354
- EVEN MORE DISAPPOINTED.

23:34.421 --> 23:36.256
YOU JUST THOUGHT A MEAL AND
A SMILE WOULD CHANGE MY MIND?

23:36.356 --> 23:39.059
- NO, I THOUGHT A BETTER PLAN
WOULD CHANGE YOUR MIND.

23:43.330 --> 23:45.432
COMING THROUGH THE FRONT DOORS
DURING THE DAY.

23:45.532 --> 23:47.600
DON'T HAVE TO BREAK IN.
THE VAULT WILL ALREADY BE OPEN.

23:47.667 --> 23:49.803
TAKES OFF A MINUTE, 45
OF OUR TIME.

23:50.070 --> 23:51.705
- WE NEED A CREW FOR THAT.

23:51.805 --> 23:53.540
I CAN'T GET ONE ASSEMBLED
THAT FAST.

23:53.606 --> 23:54.541
- I CAN.

23:54.607 --> 23:56.209
- OF COURSE.
YEAH, I FORGOT.

23:56.276 --> 23:57.644
YOU'RE THE PIED PIPER
OF THIEVES.

23:57.711 --> 23:59.446
- CAME THROUGH
WITH THE WHEELMAN, DIDN'T I?

23:59.512 --> 24:01.781
- [sighs]

24:03.516 --> 24:06.119
IT'S JUST NOT SMART
TO CREW UP THE DAY BEFORE.

24:06.186 --> 24:07.487
- OH, PLEASE.
THEY'RE HIRED GUNS.

24:07.554 --> 24:09.255
ALL THEY HAVE TO DO IS TAKE CARE
OF THE HOSTAGES.

24:09.322 --> 24:12.525
WE DO THE REST.

24:12.592 --> 24:15.395
GET YOUR BALLS UP, MAN.

24:22.235 --> 24:24.437
[door closes]
[sighs]

24:24.504 --> 24:25.438
- ARE WE IN?

24:25.505 --> 24:27.407
- MIKE, WE GOT TWO HOURS
TO PUT TOGETHER

24:27.474 --> 24:30.343
AIRTIGHT ALIASES TO CONVINCE
AMBER THAT WE'RE HIRED GUNMEN.

24:30.410 --> 24:31.678
- I ALREADY GOT
JAKES AND JOHNNY ON IT.

24:31.778 --> 24:34.381
- GREAT.
- AND BRIGGS?

24:34.447 --> 24:36.016
- SHE'S NOT COMFORTABLE
TAKING HOSTAGES

24:36.082 --> 24:37.250
WITH LESS THAN
FOUR GUNMEN.

24:37.317 --> 24:39.052
I'D ASK SOMEBODY ELSE,
BUT THERE'S NO TIME.

24:39.152 --> 24:41.254
- NO, NO, IT'S FINE.
I CAN KEEP AN EYE ON BRIGGS.

24:41.321 --> 24:44.524
- GREAT.

24:44.591 --> 24:47.260
- COME ON.

24:53.266 --> 24:54.667
- I FEEL BUTT-NAKED
WITHOUT MY GUN.

24:54.734 --> 24:57.170
- AMBER'S
SPECIFIC INSTRUCTIONS.

24:57.237 --> 24:58.605
- WHAT DO WE GOT?

24:58.671 --> 25:02.108
- WE GOT JOHN,
PAUL, MIKE, AND PAIGE.

25:02.175 --> 25:04.411
THEY'LL BE COVERING
THE PERIMETER AND THE HOSTAGES.

25:04.477 --> 25:06.713
- NICE TO SEE YOU AGAIN.
- YOU TOO.

25:07.013 --> 25:08.515
NICE TO MEET YOU,
BUT FROM NOW ON,

25:08.581 --> 25:10.583
YOU DON'T HAVE NAMES.

25:10.650 --> 25:11.618
YOU'RE ANIMALS.

25:11.718 --> 25:14.454
- [chuckles]
OH, YOU'RE SERIOUS.

25:14.521 --> 25:17.257
- WE DON'T WANT THE HOSTAGES
KNOWING ANYTHING ABOUT US.

25:17.323 --> 25:20.794
SO THE GOAT, HER GLOCK,
AND MYSELF, THE MONKEY,

25:21.061 --> 25:22.529
WILL HEAD STRAIGHT BACK
TO THE VAULT.

25:22.595 --> 25:24.431
IT'LL TAKE EXACTLY
4 MINUTES AND 13 SECONDS

25:24.497 --> 25:25.598
TO CLEAR THE VAULT.

25:25.698 --> 25:27.333
WE'LL NEED SOMEONE
TO TRANSPORT THE CASH

25:27.434 --> 25:29.469
TO THE VAN WHILE WE PACK IT.
- I'LL DO IT.

25:29.536 --> 25:32.072
- I DON'T THINK SO.
I GOT IT.

25:32.172 --> 25:33.573
- I LIKE THE ENTHUSIASM, BOYS,

25:33.640 --> 25:35.575
BUT I DON'T LET THE GUY
WHO WANTS TO CARRY THE CASH

25:35.642 --> 25:37.510
BE IN CHARGE
OF CARRYING THE CASH.

25:37.577 --> 25:38.711
HOPE YOU UNDERSTAND.

25:39.012 --> 25:43.316
THE INNOCENT SHEEP
CARRIES THE CASH.

25:46.286 --> 25:49.222
YOU LOOK LIKE YOU SHOULD WORK
IN A BANK, NOT ROB ONE.

25:49.322 --> 25:53.626
- THAT'S HOW
THEY NEVER SEE ME COMING.

25:53.726 --> 25:57.664
- THE RABBIT WATCHES THE DOOR.

25:57.764 --> 25:59.766
SLY FOX...

26:00.033 --> 26:01.401
IN THE GETAWAY VAN.

26:01.501 --> 26:03.670
THE PIG HERDS THE HOSTAGES
INTO THE BACK OFFICE,

26:03.770 --> 26:05.371
KEEPS THEM UNDER CONTROL.

26:05.438 --> 26:07.107
- NO, WHY I GOT TO BE THE PIG?
- 'CAUSE IT'S A NATURAL FIT.

26:07.207 --> 26:08.608
- LOOK, I'M LIKE MR. PINK
OVER HERE.

26:08.675 --> 26:13.179
HOW AM I GONNA INTIMIDATE
HOSTAGES WITH A PIG ON?

26:13.246 --> 26:16.349
THANKS.

26:16.449 --> 26:19.752
- MR. TIGER CUTS
THE SECURITY VIDEO,

26:20.053 --> 26:21.387
THEN HELPS
WITH THE HOSTAGES.

26:21.488 --> 26:24.090
ONE LAST THING...

26:24.157 --> 26:27.660
IF YOU TRY AND SCREW ME,
I'LL LEAVE YOU IN THE GROUND.

26:27.760 --> 26:30.230
- IS THAT NECESSARY?

26:30.296 --> 26:32.398
- OH...

26:32.499 --> 26:34.667
YOU'RE THE MYSTERY MAN.

26:34.767 --> 26:36.136
HMM?

26:36.236 --> 26:38.271
I WAS WONDERING
IF SHE'D BRING YOU.

26:38.371 --> 26:40.573
HMM.

26:40.673 --> 26:43.409
BUT YOUR GUNS WERE LOADED,
AND NONE OF YOU HESITATED.

26:43.510 --> 26:44.444
I LIKE THAT.

26:44.511 --> 26:46.379
TOMORROW, 8:00 A.M. SHARP,

26:46.479 --> 26:48.214
I WANT YOU ALL TO KNOW
THIS FLOOR PLAN

26:48.281 --> 26:49.582
BETTER THAN
YOUR MOTHER'S FACE.

26:49.649 --> 26:51.351
WE'LL DO RUN-THROUGHS
FOR TWO HOURS,

26:51.417 --> 26:54.387
GO HOME,
GET A GOOD NIGHT'S SLEEP.

27:13.439 --> 27:15.642
- YOU KNOW WHAT
THIS PLACE IS?

27:15.708 --> 27:19.279
- I KNOW EXACTLY
WHAT THIS PLACE IS.

27:19.345 --> 27:21.447
YOU KILLED
EVERYONE HERE.

27:21.548 --> 27:23.249
- YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU'RE RIGHT.

27:23.316 --> 27:26.753
WE BOTH DID.

27:27.020 --> 27:31.357
THIS PLACE BURNED
BECAUSE OF US.

27:31.424 --> 27:33.693
- SO EVERYONE HAS
HIS PRICE, RIGHT?

27:33.760 --> 27:36.296
YOU KNOW, I NEVER THOUGHT
I WOULD FIND MINE

27:36.362 --> 27:38.164
AT THE END OF A NEEDLE,
BUT YOU MADE SURE OF THAT,

27:38.231 --> 27:39.799
DIDN'T YOU?

27:40.066 --> 27:42.735
DIDN'T YOU?

27:43.036 --> 27:46.239
AND YOU LIT THE MATCH!

27:46.339 --> 27:47.740
- STAY BACK.

27:47.807 --> 27:50.176
- GUNS NOW?

27:50.243 --> 27:53.479
[gunshot]

27:55.181 --> 27:56.716
- I GUESS IT WAS
ONLY A MATTER OF TIME, HUH?

27:57.016 --> 27:59.219
- ARE YOU JUST HAVING FUN,

27:59.319 --> 28:02.555
OR DO YOU WANT
SOMETHING, MIKE?

28:02.622 --> 28:05.225
- BOTH.
- HMM.

28:05.325 --> 28:07.727
- SIT.
- [chuckles]

28:07.794 --> 28:11.598
- YOU'RE NOT A MURDERER.
- NO...

28:11.698 --> 28:14.200
BUT YOU ARE.
- HMM.

28:14.267 --> 28:16.769
YOU HAVEN'T TURNED IT IN YET.

28:19.606 --> 28:22.208
- HOW CAN YOU BE SO SURE?

28:22.308 --> 28:24.577
- BECAUSE YOU
STILL NEED ME.

30:00.506 --> 30:02.141
- PAUL.

30:02.241 --> 30:04.210
- WHAT?
[baby babbles]

30:04.277 --> 30:06.045
- YOU CAN'T DO THIS TO US.

30:06.145 --> 30:08.147
- I'M NOT.

30:14.420 --> 30:17.223
- YOU OKAY?

30:17.290 --> 30:19.092
- YEAH.

30:19.158 --> 30:21.027
YEAH, I THINK I'M GOOD.

30:21.094 --> 30:23.029
- YOU WALKING
IN YOUR SLEEP NOW?

30:23.096 --> 30:24.564
- [exhales deeply]

30:24.630 --> 30:27.400
YEAH, I GUESS SO.

30:27.467 --> 30:29.569
LET'S, UM--
LET'S GO BACK TO BED.

30:29.635 --> 30:31.137
- YOU KNOW, IN A COUPLE MONTHS,

30:31.204 --> 30:33.740
WE'RE GONNA HAVE A LITTLE
MONSTER MOVING AROUND IN THERE--

30:33.806 --> 30:35.742
OUR LITTLE MONSTER.

30:37.443 --> 30:40.012
WE'RE GONNA TALK ABOUT
WHETHER IT'S A BOY OR A GIRL,

30:40.079 --> 30:41.180
WHAT WE'RE GONNA NAME IT.

30:41.247 --> 30:43.449
ARE WE GONNA RAISE IT
CATHOLIC OR BUDDHIST?

30:43.549 --> 30:46.486
BUT ALL THAT, PAUL...
IF WE DON'T TALK,

30:46.586 --> 30:50.123
WE CAN'T HAVE
THOSE CONVERSATIONS.

30:50.189 --> 30:53.292
- WE TALK.

30:53.359 --> 30:56.329
WE'RE TALKING.

30:56.429 --> 30:59.298
- I CAN DO THIS ALONE.
I JUST DON'T WANT TO.

31:01.167 --> 31:03.202
- YOU WON'T HAVE TO.

31:03.302 --> 31:05.505
LISTEN, ONCE WE GET
THIS BANK JOB OUT OF THE WAY,

31:05.605 --> 31:07.740
I THINK I'LL BE ABLE
TO CLEAR MY HEAD.

31:09.575 --> 31:11.010
- OKAY.

31:11.077 --> 31:12.044
- OKAY.

31:12.111 --> 31:13.279
- PAUL...

31:13.346 --> 31:16.416
- HEY, CHARLIE...

31:16.482 --> 31:19.018
IT'S GONNA BE FINE.

31:21.354 --> 31:23.556
I PROMISE.

31:34.983 --> 31:37.286
- EARLY'S JUST AS BAD AS LATE.

31:37.353 --> 31:39.488
- YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHY I'M HERE YET.

31:39.555 --> 31:41.223
- WHATEVER'S
BETWEEN YOU AND HER,

31:41.290 --> 31:44.126
I'M SURE YOU'RE SMART ENOUGH
TO PUT IT ASIDE FOR THE JOB.

31:44.226 --> 31:47.529
- YOU MAY BE RIGHT ABOUT THAT,
BUT, UH, I'M NOT SURE SHE IS.

31:47.629 --> 31:49.531
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

31:49.598 --> 31:51.467
- IF YOU KNOW HER, YOU KNOW
SHE TENDS TO MIX THE PERSONAL

31:51.533 --> 31:52.668
AND THE PROFESSIONAL.

31:52.968 --> 31:54.069
IT CLOUDS HER JUDGMENT.

31:54.136 --> 31:57.573
SOMETIMES SHE HIRES
THE WRONG PEOPLE.

31:57.673 --> 32:00.209
- LIKE YOU?

32:00.309 --> 32:03.612
- LIKE THE RABBIT.
- MIKE?

32:03.712 --> 32:06.148
- A FRIEND OF MINE DID A STICKUP
JOB WITH HIM A WHILE BACK.

32:06.215 --> 32:09.017
TURNS OUT THE RABBIT
TOOK THE MONEY AND RAN.

32:09.084 --> 32:11.320
- CHARLIE PICKED HIM.

32:11.387 --> 32:13.555
I TRUST HER.

32:13.622 --> 32:16.191
- SHE PICKED ME TOO.

32:16.291 --> 32:19.294
- TAKEN UNDER ADVISEMENT.

32:19.395 --> 32:20.662
DON'T WORRY.

32:20.929 --> 32:22.164
IF HE TRIES ANYTHING FUNNY,

32:22.264 --> 32:24.700
I WON'T HESITATE
TO PUT HIM DOWN.

32:27.336 --> 32:29.304
- I BELIEVE YOU.

33:09.211 --> 33:11.513
- MOVE! EVERYBODY
ON THE GROUND RIGHT NOW!

33:11.613 --> 33:13.315
- HEY, HEY, HEY,
DON'T DO IT!

33:13.382 --> 33:15.083
- EVERYBODY STAY CALM,
AND NO ONE GETS HURT!

33:15.150 --> 33:17.252
- GIVE ME YOUR GUN!
- MOVE IT, LADY!

33:17.352 --> 33:18.987
- DON'T YOU TOUCH THAT!

33:19.054 --> 33:20.389
- LET'S GO, LET'S GO!
A LITTLE FASTER!

33:20.489 --> 33:22.124
COME ON, MOVE IT!
- MOVE IT! MOVE IT!

33:22.224 --> 33:23.525
- LET'S GO!
LET'S GET TO THE BACK ROOM!

33:23.625 --> 33:25.327
GO, GO!

33:25.394 --> 33:27.162
- STUPID MOVE, LADY!

33:27.229 --> 33:28.197
TIME!

33:28.263 --> 33:29.665
- IN THE BACK!
IN THE BACK OFFICE!

33:29.965 --> 33:31.700
BACK OFFICE, COME ON!
- LET'S GO! LET'S GO!

33:31.967 --> 33:33.235
- NOT SMART, LADY,
NOT SMART!

33:33.302 --> 33:34.236
LET'S GO!
LET'S GO!

33:47.516 --> 33:48.617
- DON'T DO IT! DON'T DO IT!
COME ON!

33:48.684 --> 33:50.686
IN THE BACK! IN THE BACK!
- GO! GO!

33:50.986 --> 33:51.954
- GET IN THE BACK ROOM!

33:52.020 --> 33:53.522
- MOVE TO THE BACK!
- LET'S GO!

33:53.622 --> 33:54.990
- KEEP MOVING!
LET'S GO!

33:55.057 --> 33:56.959
IN THE BACK OFFICE!
LET'S GO! LET'S GO!

33:57.025 --> 33:58.160
KEEP MOVING, LADY!
GO!

34:16.545 --> 34:18.380
- LET'S GO!
MOVE!

34:18.447 --> 34:19.381
- HURRY UP!
- MOVE!

34:19.448 --> 34:21.350
- GET AGAINST THE WALL!
GO! GO! GO!

34:21.416 --> 34:22.985
UP AGAINST THE WALL!

34:26.421 --> 34:29.057
- WE'RE FEDERAL AGENTS, OKAY?

34:29.124 --> 34:30.993
KEEP QUIET,
AND YOU'LL BE OKAY.

34:31.093 --> 34:34.263
NOD YOUR HEADS
SO I KNOW YOU UNDERSTAND ME.

34:34.363 --> 34:35.264
GOOD.

34:35.364 --> 34:38.166
- 2 MINUTES AND 48 SECONDS.

34:47.009 --> 34:49.611
[boom]

34:54.616 --> 34:56.451
- IT'S ALL RIGHT.
RELAX.

35:02.391 --> 35:04.159
- JACKPOT.
- YEAH.

35:07.996 --> 35:09.698
- WHAT ARE YOU
LOOKING AT, HUH, MAN?

35:09.965 --> 35:11.567
- NOTHING.
I WASN'T LOOKING AT NOTHING.

35:11.667 --> 35:13.135
- YOU KNOW WHAT, PAIGE?
KEEP AN EYE ON THIS ONE, OKAY?

35:13.201 --> 35:14.136
HE'S UP TO SOMETHING.

35:14.202 --> 35:15.137
- NO, I HAVE
TO GO GET THE MONEY.

35:15.203 --> 35:16.438
- HE'S ON SOME HERO SH--, OKAY?

35:16.505 --> 35:18.440
HE ALMOST DREW HIS GUN
AND SHOT ME OUT IN THE LOBBY.

35:18.540 --> 35:20.275
- STICK TO THE PLAN.

35:20.342 --> 35:23.078
- SOMETIMES PLANS CHANGE.
WATCH HIM.

35:25.080 --> 35:26.181
[door closes]

35:26.248 --> 35:28.951
- HEY, RABBIT,
HOSTAGES ARE GETTING UNRULY.

35:29.051 --> 35:31.687
YOU GONNA GET THE MONEY,
OR SHOULD I?

35:31.954 --> 35:34.556
- I'LL GET THE CASH.

35:38.093 --> 35:40.262
- ALMOST DONE.
ONE MORE BAG AFTER THIS.

35:40.329 --> 35:41.930
- OKAY, GOOD.
WE GOT TO WRAP THIS UP.

35:42.030 --> 35:45.467
IT'S TIME TO GET
OUT OF HERE.

35:45.567 --> 35:49.237
- I'LL TAKE THIS BAG
TO THE VAN.

35:49.338 --> 35:50.939
- WHERE THE HELL'S SHEEP?

35:51.039 --> 35:52.274
- HE'S TIED UP
WITH THE HOSTAGES.

35:52.341 --> 35:55.010
- [exhales deeply]
GREEDY SCUMBAG.

35:55.077 --> 35:56.411
- WHAT?

35:56.478 --> 35:57.646
- TIGER WARNED ME ABOUT HIM.

35:57.946 --> 36:00.315
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
- CLEANING UP YOUR MESS.

36:00.382 --> 36:02.684
- WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?
- MAYBE YOU DIDN'T KNOW,

36:02.951 --> 36:04.686
OR MAYBE YOU'RE TRYING
TO SCREW ME TOO.

36:04.987 --> 36:06.722
ALL I'M SAYING IS THIS IS WHY
YOU DON'T CHANGE PLANS

36:06.989 --> 36:08.123
THE DAY BEFORE.
- AMBER--

36:08.223 --> 36:09.358
- NOW I'M GONNA GO PUT A BULLET

36:09.424 --> 36:12.327
IN YOUR FRIEND
WHO TOOK MY MONEY.

36:12.394 --> 36:14.363
- MIKE!

36:31.113 --> 36:34.182
[cell phone vibrating]

36:35.283 --> 36:38.553
- THIS PLACE BURNED
BECAUSE OF US.

36:38.654 --> 36:40.589
- BUT EVERYONE
HAS HIS PRICE, RIGHT?

36:40.656 --> 36:42.524
- YOU LIT THE MATCH!

36:42.624 --> 36:44.693
- STAY BACK.
- GUNS NOW?

36:44.960 --> 36:46.361
[gunshot]
- [screams]

37:10.419 --> 37:13.321
[background chatter]

37:13.422 --> 37:17.125
[sirens wailing]

37:20.328 --> 37:22.397
- THEY DONE WITH YOU?

37:22.497 --> 37:24.533
- WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED
IN THERE, PAUL?

37:24.599 --> 37:27.002
[tires screeching]

37:27.069 --> 37:28.003
- COME ON, WE GOT TO GO.

37:28.103 --> 37:29.438
- NO, WAIT.
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU.

37:29.504 --> 37:32.307
- CHARLIE, COME ON,
WE GOT TO GO.

37:36.011 --> 37:37.479
[Sid groans]

37:39.581 --> 37:41.116
- HEY, TOMMY.

37:41.183 --> 37:43.585
HEY, MAN, WHAT'S GOING ON?

37:51.259 --> 37:53.495
SO IT WAS ALL
AN UNDERCOVER OP BY--

37:53.562 --> 37:58.100
DRUMROLL--YOUR BOY
SPECIAL AGENT MIKE WARREN.

37:58.166 --> 38:00.302
PERP GOT AWAY.
THE BUST WENT SOUR.

38:00.402 --> 38:03.638
- YEAH, IT WENT SOUR,
ALL RIGHT.

38:03.705 --> 38:07.509
- I'LL DO A LITTLE DIGGING,
SEE WHAT I CAN FIND OUT.

38:07.576 --> 38:10.212
- I SPOKE WITH AGENT AMADIO,
BUCKNAM, AND DEHOOP.

38:10.278 --> 38:11.613
NONE OF THIS WAS APPROVED.

38:11.680 --> 38:13.248
- I'M SORRY, SIR.
THE PLAN CHANGED,

38:13.348 --> 38:14.950
BUT THE MISSION
REMAINED THE SAME--

38:15.016 --> 38:17.052
TO TAKE MARKHAM'S MONEY
OUT OF PLAY.

38:17.119 --> 38:20.088
- YOU DESTROYED BANK PROPERTY,
PUT INNOCENT HOSTAGES AT RISK.

38:20.155 --> 38:22.657
YOU'RE LESS THAN A WEEK OUTSIDE
THIS BLOODBATH IN SYLMAR.

38:22.924 --> 38:24.993
I SWEAR TO GOD, IF I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE SUCH A LADDER-CLIMBER,

38:25.060 --> 38:27.062
I'D THINK YOU WERE TRYING
TO CANNONBALL YOUR OWN CAREER.

38:27.129 --> 38:30.065
ARE YOU EVEN LISTENING
TO ME RIGHT NOW?

38:30.165 --> 38:32.200
- YES, SIR.

38:32.267 --> 38:34.302
I KNOW IT MAY
NOT LOOK LIKE IT,

38:34.369 --> 38:36.471
BUT I HAVE THIS
UNDER CONTROL.

38:36.538 --> 38:38.573
IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME...

38:40.308 --> 38:42.144
- WARREN!

38:42.210 --> 38:44.613
- YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
TO TRUST ME.

38:44.679 --> 38:46.648
- THIS IS SUICIDE, WARREN.

38:48.717 --> 38:50.552
- HEY, SID.

38:50.619 --> 38:52.387
YOU MUST FEEL
PRETTY STUPID, HUH?

38:52.487 --> 38:53.588
- HOW'S THAT?

38:53.655 --> 38:56.091
- YOU PUT YOUR OWN NAME
ON THE SAFE-DEPOSIT BOXES.

38:56.191 --> 38:57.659
- I LIKE MY NAME.

38:57.959 --> 39:00.095
WHERE'S YOUR BANK ROBBER?

39:00.195 --> 39:01.663
- I THINK YOU HAVE
MORE IMPORTANT THINGS

39:01.963 --> 39:04.432
TO BE WORRIED ABOUT,
DETECTIVE MARKHAM.

39:04.499 --> 39:07.369
- SEE, THE THING IS...

39:07.469 --> 39:10.172
THERE'S NOTHING ON MY WRISTS.

39:10.238 --> 39:12.440
- I CAN JUST HOLD ON
TO THIS FOR YOU.

39:12.507 --> 39:14.943
UNLESS YOU WANT TO CLAIM IT.

39:16.511 --> 39:19.381
- I'M GONNA SEE YOU AROUND.

39:25.654 --> 39:28.623
[jazz music]

39:28.690 --> 39:30.625
♪ ♪

39:30.926 --> 39:32.260
- YOU JUST MISSED OUR TURN.

39:32.360 --> 39:34.996
♪ ♪

39:35.096 --> 39:38.033
WHERE ARE YOU TAKING ME?

39:38.133 --> 39:40.402
- TO THE DESERT.
I WANT TO SHOW YOU SOMETHING.

39:40.502 --> 39:42.537
- SHOW ME WHAT?

39:42.637 --> 39:44.139
- I WANT TO SHOW YOU
THE TRUTH, CHARLIE.

39:44.239 --> 39:45.941
- NO, I DON'T WANT
TO HEAR IT ANYMORE.

39:46.007 --> 39:48.577
JUST TAKE ME HOME.

39:51.513 --> 39:54.349
TURN AROUND, PAUL.

39:54.416 --> 39:57.285
- YOU KNOW WHAT?
I HAVE BEEN SLEEPWALKING...

39:57.352 --> 39:59.454
FOR MONTHS.
SH--, FOR YEARS.

39:59.554 --> 40:01.389
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW IT.

40:01.456 --> 40:03.291
YOU HAVE BEEN ASKING ME
TO TALK.

40:03.391 --> 40:04.459
AND YOU'RE RIGHT.

40:04.526 --> 40:07.629
THERE'S THINGS
YOU NEED TO HEAR, BABE...

40:07.696 --> 40:09.264
TO SEE,

40:09.331 --> 40:11.600
THINGS YOU COULD NEVER
POSSIBLY--

40:11.666 --> 40:14.402
[loud crash,
tires screeching]

40:28.416 --> 40:31.353
BABY, CALL THE SHERIFF.

40:31.453 --> 40:33.088
- PAUL.
- CALL ANIMAL CONTROL.

40:33.188 --> 40:34.623
SHE'S STILL ALIVE.

40:34.723 --> 40:36.057
- TAKE ME HOME.

40:36.157 --> 40:37.425
- COME ON, HER RIBS ARE BROKEN.
SHE'S GOT INTERNAL--

40:37.492 --> 40:39.427
[gunshot]

40:41.062 --> 40:43.698
- YOU LIT THE MATCH, PAUL.

40:52.340 --> 40:54.309
- HOW LONG?

40:56.278 --> 40:57.946
HOW LONG HAVE
YOU HAD THE TAPE?

40:58.046 --> 41:00.448
- COUPLE OF WEEKS.

41:02.417 --> 41:05.320
- THAT'S WHY YOU LEFT THE HOUSE?
- GOD, NO.

41:06.721 --> 41:10.191
I LEFT THE HOUSE
'CAUSE I KNEW I WAS PREGNANT.

41:10.292 --> 41:11.960
THAT SAME GODDAMN NIGHT
I GET A CALL

41:12.060 --> 41:16.031
FROM A FRIEND AT THE LAPD,
AND HE PLAYS THE TAPE AND...

41:17.599 --> 41:20.435
WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST TELL ME?

41:23.538 --> 41:27.475
I GAVE YOU EVERY CHANCE...

41:27.542 --> 41:29.477
EVERY CHANCE.

41:29.544 --> 41:31.713
- I WAS GONNA TELL YOU.
- NO.

41:31.980 --> 41:34.582
YOU WERE GONNA KILL MIKE.

41:34.649 --> 41:36.584
[voice breaking]
INSTEAD OF COMING TO ME,

41:36.651 --> 41:39.621
INSTEAD OF TRUSTING ME,
YOU TURNED TO MURDER.

41:42.023 --> 41:45.193
YOUR PLAN WAS TO MURDER MIKE.

